sutro-integration:

- **Not affiliated**: This plugin bundle is a community/dev-agents template. Official Sutro docs live at [docs.withsutro.com](https://docs.withsutro.com).
- **SLang**: Use the **slang** skill in this repo for syntax and patterns. Prefer SLang files (e.g. `*.slang`) when defining backends; align edits with Sutro Studio or the Sutro API when the user’s workflow uses those.
- **MCP auth**: The `mcp/sutro` server reads the **security bundle** from `SUTRO_SECURITY_BUNDLE_DIR` (see [building full-stack / bundle](https://docs.withsutro.com/docs/getting-started/building-full-stack-apps)): mTLS (`ca.crt`, `mtls.crt`, `mtls.key`), `builder.jwt` (Bearer), and `apiClient.id` (`x-sutro-api-client`). Optional `SUTRO_API_BASE` defaults to `https://sapi.withsutro.com`. If `builder.jwt` is stale, the server can refresh it locally using `signing.pem` (preferred) or `mtls.key` plus issuer/sub metadata in the bundle. Never print JWTs, private keys, or PEMs in tool output.
- **Official skill updates**: The vendored `skills/slang/SKILL.md` comes from [SutroOrg/sutro-skills](https://github.com/SutroOrg/sutro-skills). Refresh it periodically to stay in sync with SLang changes.

## MCP tools

| Tool | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `sutro_hello` | Calls `GET /hello` to verify bundle credentials and connectivity |
| `sutro_validate_bundle` | Checks bundle files/metadata and verifies auth-readiness before API calls |
| `sutro_list_projects` | List all projects visible to the authenticated builder |
| `sutro_list_apps` | List applications, optionally filtered by `projectId` |
| `sutro_get_app` | Get application details; pass `includeScode=true` for full SCode |
| `sutro_get_app_status` | Get current job/deployment status for an application |
| `sutro_get_openapi` | Get the OpenAPI spec for an application |
| `sutro_deploy_slang` | Compile SLang and update an application (surfaces compile errors) |
| `sutro_publish_app` | Publish an application live; optionally bump `major`/`minor`/`patch` |
| `sutro_list_secrets` | List secret names configured on an application (values never returned) |
| `sutro_set_secret` | Add or update a secret on an application |
| `sutro_delete_secret` | Remove a secret from an application |
